cs.LG, cs.ST, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a kernel-based nonparametric approach for detecting change-points in data, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The paper focuses on the scenario when the amount of background data is large, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes a novel theoretical result for characterizing the tail probability of the proposed statistics, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.ST (Statistics). The paper uses a change-of-measure technique, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also applies the proposed method to high-dimensional data, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
